If you redistribute modified sources, I would appreciate that you
include in the files history information documenting your changes.



DejaVu fonts can be found inside this repository at:
    bbb/meta-bbb/recipes-core/trebletrouble/files/src/ugfx/resources/ugfx/src/gdisp/fonts/

DejaVu fonts are not part of the uGFX Library. They are distributed under a BSD-like license.
See COPYING.DejaVu for details.

Fonts are (c) Bitstream (see COPYING.DejaVu). DejaVu changes are in public domain.



Poky can be found inside this repository at:
    poky-krogoth/

As an integration layer Poky consists of several upstream projects such as 
BitBake, OpenEmbedded-Core, Yocto documentation and various sources of information 
e.g. for the hardware support. Poky is in turn a component of the Yocto Project.

The Yocto Project has extensive documentation about the system including a 
reference manual which can be found at:
    http://yoctoproject.org/documentation


BitBake is licensed under the GNU General Public License version 2.0.
See COPYING.GPLv2 for further details.

The following external components are distributed with BitBake:

    * The Toaster Simple UI application is based upon the Django project
      template, the files of which are covered by the BSD license and are
      copyright (c) Django Software Foundation and individual contributors.

    * Twitter Bootstrap (including Glyphicons), redistributed under the
      Apache License 2.0.

    * jQuery is redistributed under the MIT license.

    * QUnit is redistributed under the MIT license.


Different components of OpenEmbedded are under different licenses (a mix
of MIT and GPLv2). Please see:

    COPYING.GPLv2 (GPLv2)
    COPYING.MIT (MIT)

For information about OpenEmbedded, see the OpenEmbedded website:
    http://www.openembedded.org/

